# UI Components with shadcn/ui

## Component Library Usage

- Use [`shadcn/ui`](https://ui.shadcn.com) for consistent and accessible UI components
- Follow the established design system and component patterns
- Customize components through props and CSS variables
- Maintain component consistency across the application

## Component Customization

- Override component styles using CSS variables
- Extend components with additional props when needed
- Maintain accessibility standards when customizing
- Document component customizations and usage patterns

## Component Organization

- Place UI components in `components/ui/` directory
- Group related components in subdirectories
- Create wrapper components for complex UI patterns
- Implement proper component composition patterns

## Theming and Styling

- Use CSS custom properties for theme customization
- Implement dark/light mode support when needed
- Maintain consistent color palette and typography
- Use design tokens for spacing and sizing

## Accessibility Standards

- Ensure all components meet WCAG accessibility guidelines
- Implement proper ARIA attributes and labels
- Support keyboard navigation and screen readers
- Test components with accessibility tools

## Component Documentation

- Document component props and usage examples
- Provide Storybook stories for complex components
- Include accessibility notes and keyboard shortcuts
- Maintain up-to-date component documentation

## Performance Considerations

- Lazy load heavy UI components when possible
- Optimize component re-renders with proper memoization
- Use proper loading states for async components
- Implement proper error boundaries for UI components

## Component Testing

- Write unit tests for component logic and interactions
- Implement visual regression tests for UI components
- Test accessibility features and keyboard navigation
- Ensure components work across different browsers and devices
